description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3 Clinical Support Worker/Occupational Therapy Assistant 1.0 WTE, Permanent contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a committed Band 3 Occupational Therapy Assistant to work as part of our acute mental health, inpatient occupational therapy team at Mill View Hospital, in the vibrant city of Brighton and Hove.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be based on Meridian older adult ward, working alongside the ward occupational therapist. You will be responsible for delivering a range of occupation and psychoeducation focused group and 1:1interventions, to patients with acute mental health needs and additional needs. You will use meaningful activity to promote the health, wellbeing and recovery of patients on the ward, as part of their overall multidisciplinary care plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the wider Mill View OT service, you may be required to provide group interventions on our other acute admissions wards as part of your role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome candidates with effective communication and organization skills, a person-centered, enabling approach, able to demonstrate confidence and self-awareness and above all a compassionate, caring attitude and desire to make a difference. Skills and experience in running groups is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your skills and commitment we can offer you interesting and highly rewarding work within a supportive, established occupational therapy team that prides itself on providing the highest standard of patient care. We will offer you regular learning and development opportunities and clinical supervision. The successful candidate will receive support, guidance and supervision from the ward Occupational Therapist. Furthermore, the organization provides excellent training opportunities, regular learning events and networks with a professional structure in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time and there will be some expectation of evening and weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are flexible, committed, creative, caring and forward thinking, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire MichieAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Specialist Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mill View Hospital &lt;br /&gt;Nevill Avenue &lt;br /&gt;Hove &lt;br /&gt;BN3 7HZ &lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01273 621984 ext 201058&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mobile: 07391408532&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note my working hours: Mondays 8.30-15.00, Tuesday 8.30-17.00, Wednesdays 8.30-19.00 and Saturdays 9.00-15.00&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
